1)lecture de la table

#1)lecture de la table
clim <- read.table("Volume de production clim.txt", header=F)
clim<-clim$V1
#janvier 1992 au mois de mars 2014
mts=ts(clim,start=c(1992,1),frequency=12)
plot(mts)

boxplot(mts~cycle(mts))

d1<-decompose(mts,type="additive")
plot(d1)

a) vecteur temps

tps<-1:length(clim)

b) modèle ax+b

mod1<-lm(clim~tps)
plot(clim,type="l")
points(time(clim), fitted(mod1), type="l", col="blue")

4) introduction de la saisonnalité

a) sinus et cosinus

MC<-matrix(0, length(clim), 6)
MS<-matrix(0, length(clim), 6)

for (i in 1:dim(MC)[2]) MC[,i]<-cos((2*pi*tps)/(12/i))
for (i in 1:dim(MS)[2]) MS[,i]<-sin((2*pi*tps)/(12/i))

mod4<-lm(log(clim)~ntps+MC+MS)
plot(clim,type="l")
points(time(clim), exp(fitted(mod4)), type="l", col="red")

summary(mod4)
